<header class="header">
  <h1>Too Late to Start Tomatoes in Zone 5?</h1>

  <p class="tagline">
    Zone 5 is short-season — but timing depends on frost dates.
  </p>

  <p class="lede">
    <strong>It is usually not too late to start tomatoes in Zone 5 until 6–8 weeks before your first fall frost date.</strong>
    The real deadline depends on your average last spring frost and first fall frost — not the zone number alone.
  </p>

  <p>
    To calculate your personal seed-start and transplant windows,
